from typing import List

class Solution:
    def minDeletionSize(self, strs: List[str]) -> int:
        m, n = len(strs), len(strs[0])

        # dp[i] will store the length of the longest increasing subsequence ending at index i
        dp = [1] * n

        for i in range(n):
            for j in range(i):
                if all(strs[k][j] <= strs[k][i] for k in range(m)):
                    dp[i] = max(dp[i], dp[j] + 1)

        # The maximum length of increasing subsequence gives us the columns to keep
        # The minimum number of deletions is the total number of columns minus this length
        return n - max(dp)
```

This solution uses dynamic programming to find the longest increasing subsequence of columns that can be kept to ensure each row is lexicographically ordered. The number of deletions required is the total number of columns minus the length of this subsequence.
